<template><div><h1 id="hiding-a-component-form-in-design-time" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#hiding-a-component-form-in-design-time" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Hiding a component form in Design-Time</h1>
<p><code v-pre>TCompoManEh</code> component
<code v-pre>TCompoManEh</code> component is intended for use only in the <code v-pre>Design-Time</code>.
<code v-pre>TCompoManEh</code> can hide other components form during development, thereby enabling to see the design of the form as close to the design mode <code v-pre>Run-Time</code>.</p>
<p><img src="@source/images/clip0008.png" alt="" loading="lazy"></p>
<p>The upper screenshot the form is whown at <code v-pre>Desig-Time</code>.
All components, except the <code v-pre>TCompoManEh</code>, are hidden by a component editor <code v-pre>CompoManEh1</code>. The right side of the screenshot you can see a window with a list of hidden components. The window opens when you double-click on <code v-pre>CompoManEh1</code>. The window contains all the components form <code v-pre>TForm2</code>. Right-click on the component from the list of Popup Menu Editor opens the selected components.</p>
</div></template>


